WEBVTT

00:01:58.642 --> 00:02:01.192
a heart attack may be silent.

00:02:01.192 --> 00:02:03.993
If you think that someone might be 
having a heart attack,

00:02:03.993 --> 00:02:07.163
the most important thing 
is to respond quickly.

00:02:07.163 --> 00:02:11.032
If you have access to emergency medical
services, call them.

00:02:11.032 --> 00:02:13.474
They're the fastest way 
to get to a hospital.

00:02:13.474 --> 00:02:15.825
Taking aspirin, which thins the blood,

00:02:15.825 --> 00:02:18.624
and nitroglycerin, 
which opens up the artery,

00:02:18.624 --> 00:02:21.594
can help keep the heart attack
from getting worse.

00:02:21.594 --> 00:02:24.933
In the emergency room, 
doctors can diagnose a heart attack.

00:02:24.933 --> 00:02:27.524
They commonly use an electrocardiogram

00:02:27.524 --> 00:02:30.034
to measure the heart's 
electrical activity